cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper is related to natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on semantic role labeling (SRL) task for Chinese language. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper proposes a new model architecture for SRL task, which involves the use of recurrent neural network (RNN) and long short-term memory (LSTM) networks. This suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of dependency parsing information, which could also relate to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) categories.
